## Out of scope

- **`CLI-WEBSITE-*`** (docs site): separate DSN, separate cleanup.
- **`CLI-BJ "Unexpected failure at line 298"`** (280 events): `install.sh` bash trap — needs its own fix in the install pipeline.
- **Real bugs surfaced**: `CLI-12Z TypeError replaceAll` (likely null-source gotcha), `CLI-19A EINVAL kqueue` — separate tickets.
- **Cleaning up inline `throw new ApiError(...)` sites** with dynamic messages (23 sites): fingerprint normalization solves the grouping symptom without code churn. Can be cleaned up opportunistically later.
- **Demoting any error class to logs-only / metrics-only** (no issue emission): explicitly out — user preference is to keep issues for UX visibility and SeerError for marketing.
